        <briefdescription>
<para>extracts a medially centered curve skeleton for the triangle mesh <computeroutput>tmesh</computeroutput>. This function uses the class <ref refid="classCGAL_1_1Mean__curvature__flow__skeletonization" kindref="compound">CGAL::Mean_curvature_flow_skeletonization</ref> with the default parameters. This function is provided only if Eigen 3.2 (or greater) is available and <computeroutput>CGAL_EIGEN3_ENABLED</computeroutput> is defined. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="pre"><para><computeroutput>tmesh</computeroutput> is a triangle mesh without borders and having exactly one connected component. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="pre"><para>The specialization <computeroutput>boost::property_map&lt;TriangleMesh, CGAL::vertex_point_t&gt;::type</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>get(vertex_point, tmesh)</computeroutput> are defined. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="pre"><para>The value type of <computeroutput>boost::property_map&lt;TriangleMesh, CGAL::vertex_point_t&gt;::type</computeroutput> is a point type from a CGAL Kernel.</para>
</simplesect>
